<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,258,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,411,403,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[799,900,404,430]" name="Morocco" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">Morocco</collectingCountry>
based on a few male specimens, showing differences in their antennae and certain features of the male genitalia (stout uncus and valval apical section, vesica without cornuti) compared with 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[514,744,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwingenschussi">
<emphasis box="[514,744,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. schwingenschussi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boursin 1954)" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[798,1109,475,502]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbaria">
<emphasis box="[798,929,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. barbaria</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boursin, C." box="[943,1101,475,502]" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" pagination="85 - 89" refId="ref7601" refString="Boursin, C. (1954) Zwei neue Cryphia Hb. (Bryophila) - Arten aus dem vorderasiatisch-mediterranean Faunenkreis. (Beitrage zur Kenntnis der &quot; Agrotidae-Trifinae &quot; 66). Zeitschrift der Wiener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 39, 85 - 89." type="journal article" year="1954">Boursin 1954</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,258,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,431,511,537]" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">External diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[439,599,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharista">
<emphasis box="[439,599,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. blepharista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[750,886,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis box="[750,886,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
externally in the shape of the omega-shaped design, in which the inner marginal line is usually at a higher position in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[933,1092,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharista">
<emphasis box="[933,1092,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. blepharista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but close to the hind margin in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[151,285,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis box="[151,285,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[450,608,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharista">
<emphasis box="[450,608,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. blepharista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows more or less pronounced antemarginal line, absent or almost absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[180,315,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis box="[180,315,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,258,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,416,655,681]" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">Genital diagnosis:</emphasis>
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[676,836,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharista">
<emphasis box="[676,836,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. blepharista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[853,934,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 7. 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1922,1946]" captionTargetBox="[276,1312,224,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[150,1438,181,1898]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. 7a. Male genitalia of Bryophila squamosa. Lectotype male, HighAtlas Mts, Morocco.Slide No.: RL12464.NHMW. 7b. Male genitalia of Bryophila schwingenschussi. Holotype male, Bône, Algeria. Slide No.: Boursin Schwi30. NHMW. 7c. Male genitalia of Bryophila blepharista. Holotype male, Taanzoult [Tazoult], Morocco. Slide No.: BoursinSchw30. MNHN." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406330/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">Fig. 7c</figureCitation>
) are seemingly stouter than those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[234,406,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[239,1379,231,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-28@10.[159,1429,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. 6a. Male genitalia of Bryophila perloides, male, Finca La Molina, Casares, Málaga, Andalusia. Genit, prep. MF, ZMC. 6b. Genitalia of the syntype of Bryophila perloides, designated here as lectotype. Andalusia, Spain. Genit, prep. Gyula M. László, NHMUK, specimen labelled as 010918082. 6c. Male genitalia of Bryophila barbaria. Lectotype male, High Atlas Mts, Morocco. Slide No.: RL12477. NHMW." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406328/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">Figs 6a and 6b</figureCitation>
), according to the short series of examined specimens; the central clasper is comparatively shorter and gracile in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[391,525,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis box="[391,525,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although in both species shows spatulate apex. On the other hand, the uncus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharista">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. blepharista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a narrow stem and incrassate subapical part, exactly like in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[1003,1138,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis box="[1003,1138,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The sacculus is short and flimsy, like in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[309,443,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis box="[309,443,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
too. Examination of larger series may clarify if these differences are actually interspecific or rather intraspecific. Epiphallus is cylindrical in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[719,879,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharista">
<emphasis box="[719,879,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. blepharista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and conical in 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke, 1825" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[1052,1188,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perloides">
<emphasis box="[1052,1188,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="66">B. perloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; but these differences may be due to different pressure of the cover glass.
</paragraph>
